feed.title: Changing the Guard
feed.eventDate: Starts at 10.45am but get there early for a good viewing spot.
feed.station: Victoria, Green Park, St Jamess Park or Hyde Park Corner
feed.description: Changing the Guard at Buckingham Palace encompasses colourful spectacle and British pageantry. During the Changing the Guard ceremony, also known as Guard Mounting, one regiment takes over from another. The Queens Guard is made up of the St Jamess Palace and Buckingham Palace detachments. The New Guard, who during the course of the ceremony become The Queens Guard, march to Buckingham Palace from Wellington Barracks with musical accompaniment.

feed.title: Winter Wonderland in Hyde Park
feed.address: Winter Wonderland Hyde Park London W2
feed.station: Victoria, Bond Street, Knightsbridge, Green Park, Marble Arch, Hyde Park Corner
feed.price: Entry to Winter Wonderland is free, tickets are for attrations inside.
feed.description: Celebrate Christmas at Hyde Parks Winter Wonderland, explore the many attrations including Ice Rink, The Magical Ice Kingdom, Peter Pan on Ice, Zippos Christmas Circus, Cirque Berserk, Teletubbies Christmas Show, Giant Wheel, Ice Sculpting Workshops, Winter Wonderland Comedy Club, Bar Hutte and Bar Ice.

feed.title: Christmas tree at Trafalgar Square
feed.description: The Trafalgar Square Christmas tree is a Christmas tree donated to the people of Britain by the city of Oslo, Norway each year since 1947. The tree is prominently displayed in Trafalgar Square from the beginning of December until 6 January.
